# gsi-cli Presentation Architecture

The CLI UI uses `App.tsx` as root composition, `CliShell` as layout shell, and an interactive organism for body flow.

## 1) Layout Ownership

- `App.tsx` owns root composition (`Provider`, `RootReduxEffects`, `InteractiveCli`).
- Bootstrap and sync hooks live in `App.tsx` as `RootReduxEffects` (child of `Provider`).
- `InteractiveCli` drives screen mode/input; body screens select from the `cliSession` slice (`useCliSession` removed).

## 2) State Boundaries

- Redux selectors/thunks remain the source of truth for app/system state.
- Local CLI navigation state maps to Redux `cliSession`; `InteractiveCli` holds `useInput` and dispatches actions.
- Config editing keeps a slice-held draft (synced from persisted config while in config mode); `saveCliConfig` runs only after explicit confirmation.

## 3) Interaction Model

- Header always shows Steam status, CS2 status, and Gateway status.
- Body mode behavior:
  - Idle gateway: `start`, `config`, `exit`
  - Online gateway: `stop`, `exit`
- Config mode supports up/down field navigation plus save/cancel.

## 4) Implementation Guardrails

- Reuse existing store contracts (`startGateway`, `stopGateway`, `saveCliConfig`, `exitCli`).
- Keep the UI terminal-first and keyboard-driven (`ink` + clear focus state).
